body:
I wanted to check if Verilator currently supports the use of array.sum() with (...) inside a constraint block.

From a quick look at the `verilator_types.h` file, I can see that the `r_sum` method appears to support a with function:
```c
template <typename T_Func>
WithFuncReturnType<T_Func> r_sum(T_Func with_func) const {
    WithFuncReturnType<T_Func> out = WithFuncReturnType<T_Func>(0);
    IData index = 0;
    for (const auto& i : m_deque) out += with_func(index++, i);
    return out;
}
```

However, when I try to use it in the following SystemVerilog constraint:
```verilog
constraint duplicates_only_c {
  foreach(array[i]) {
    array.sum() with (int'(item == array[i])) == 1;
  }
}
```

I receive the following error:
```text
%Error: unique_only.sv:25:19: 'with' not legal on this method
                                                                                                                                                         : ... note: In instance 'unique_only_top'
   25 |       array.sum() with (int'(item==array[i]))== 1;
      |                   ^~~~
```

Is the functionality supported?

